## Using ggplot2 

### Scatterplots

For use with at least two continuous variables




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
# Adding a class categorical value

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color=class))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
# adding labels

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color=class)) +
  labs(x = "engine displacement (L)",
       y = "highway fuel efficiency (mpg)",
       color = "type of vehicle",
       title = "Fuel Economy as a Function of Engine Size",
       subtitle = "Fuel Efficiency and Engine Size are Inversely Related",
       caption = "Data obtained from fueleconomy.gov")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-3.png){width=672}
:::
:::




### Trend Curves




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
## two continuous and a categorical 

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = drv))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
`geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
```


:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## include actual observations w/geom_point

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
`geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
```


:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-2.png){width=672}
:::
:::




### Time Series




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
homeruns <- readr::read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jafox11/MS282/main/homeruns.csv")
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Rows: 46 Columns: 3
── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr (1): league
dbl (2): year, home_run_total

ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = homeruns) +
  geom_line(mapping = aes(x = year, y = home_run_total))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = homeruns) +
  geom_line(mapping = aes(x = year, y = home_run_total, color = league))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = homeruns, mapping = aes(x = year, y = home_run_total, color = league)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-3.png){width=672}
:::
:::




### Box Plots




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x = drv, y = hwy))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## changing order 

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x = reorder(drv,hwy), y = hwy))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## flipping axes

ggplot(data = mpg) +
  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x = reorder(drv, hwy), y = hwy)) +
  coord_flip()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-3.png){width=672}
:::
:::




### Bar Graphs




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
## bar graph w/proportions

ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, y = stat(prop), group = 1))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Warning: `stat(prop)` was deprecated in ggplot2 3.4.0.
ℹ Please use `after_stat(prop)` instead.
```


:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## setting bins
ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_histogram(mapping = aes(x = price), binwidth = 1500)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## histogram

ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_histogram(mapping = aes(x = price))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
```


:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-3.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## position argument

ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = clarity, fill = cut), position = "dodge")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](11-Visualizations-in-R_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-4.png){width=672}
:::
:::




